title: For Sale:  Beretta 950 Jetfire .25 cal.  NEVER FIRED!
postcontent:
This collectable, single action pocket pistol was given to me as a gift many years ago and has never left my home.   As you can see in the photos, it is in new condition and has never been fired, or carried. This is the 950BS model with a safety.
One of the neat features of this pocket pistol is that you don't need to rack the slide in order to feed a round into the chamber.  You just push the release button near the trigger and the barrel pops up.  Insert a round, close the barrel and it’s ready to fire.  This provides a 9 round capacity with a full magazine.  Speaking of magazines, they are readily available from Beretta and other vendors, along with other parts and accessories.
These pistols have a l-o-n-g history and were first manufactured in Italy in 1952.  This model was made at the Beretta plant in Maryland, as seen stamped on the slide.   
After researching on the web, these typically sell for $200.00 or less for used average condition, $250.00 for used excellent condition and up to $350.00 for NIB condition. 
Original box & user manual is included.
 
No trades please.
